====Toggling Content Warning labels====
To change which labels to filter, first open your [[Special:MyLanguage/Quick Menu|Quick Menu]], then select the [[Special:MyLanguage/Main Menu|Main Menu]] button at the top right. From here, select the [[Special:MyLanguage/Settings|Settings]] tab on the Main Menu header. Then, select the "Comfort & Safety" category on the left side. Under the "Content Gating" header, is where the labels can be changed.

==Applying Content Warnings==
===SDK===
[[File:Content warnings avatar SDK.webp|thumb|Avatar SDK content warnings]]
====Avatars & worlds====
In the [[Special:MyLanguage/VRChat SDK|SDK]]'s "Builder" tab, navigate to the "Prepare Your Content" header. Select the "Content Warnings" dropdown, choose applicable content warnings, then press the "Save Changes" button at the top of the "Builder" tab.

===Website===
[[File:Content warnings website.webp|thumb|Website content warnings]]
====Avatars====
Navigate to the "{{VRC link|https://vrchat.com/home/avatars|Avatars}}" page on the VRChat website, then select an avatar. Scroll down to the "Content Warnings" section. Select applicable content warnings, and it will be automatically applied.

====Worlds====
Navigate to the "{{VRC link|https://vrchat.com/home/content/worlds|Worlds}}" page on the VRChat website, then select a world. Scroll down to the "Content Warnings" section. Select applicable content warnings, then press the "Save Changes" button at the top right of the page.

==Reporting missing Content Warnings==
Avatars or Worlds may not have any or have incorrect content warnings. These types of content can be reported using the [[Special:MyLanguage/Reporting|in-client report form]]. There is no penalty to labeling appropriately, not doing so will result in VRChat labeling it at their own discretion, one could also potentially face action against their account in some circumstances.

